#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:71
msgid "**&quot;Open&quot; versus &quot;Blind&quot; or &quot;Closed&quot; Review**"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:72
msgid ""
"&quot;Open&quot; review is a form of review in which the names of the "
"reviewers are made public."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:73
msgid ""
"&quot;Double-Open&quot; review is when the reviewers know the identity of"
" the proposal author and the proposal author also knows the identity of "
"their reviewers"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:74
msgid ""
"&quot;Double Blind&quot; review means the reviewers do not know the "
"identity of the proposal author and vice versa."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:75
msgid ""
"&quot;Single Blind&quot; or simply &quot;Blind&quot; review means that "
"the author of the proposal does not know the identity of the reviewers."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:76
msgid ""
"Sometimes the term &quot;Closed&quot; or &quot;Anonymized&quot; is used "
"instead of &quot;Blind&quot;."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:77
msgid "**Double &quot;Blind&quot; Review**"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:78
msgid ""
"By changing speaker selection to completely &quot;blind,&quot; you may be"
" able to increase representation from traditionally underrepresented "
"groups. (See &quot;Further Reading&quot; below.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:79
msgid ""
"You might create a CFP form that instructs the submitter to withhold "
"identifying information."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:80
msgid ""
"You can assign 1-2 people to remove the identifying information from "
"submissions before passing them to the next group of reviewers/the "
"assessing team."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:81
msgid ""
"However, be aware that it's not always possible to do this, particularly "
"if the work is tightly tied to the authors, or is based on their past "
"work, and that reviewers can often determine authors even when they "
"technically shouldn't. Reviewers may also search for information about "
"the subject of the work, which can lead them to a preprint of the "
"submitted material with the authors listed. In this case, you may want to"
" explicitly instruct the reviewers to try not to consider information "
"about the authors they happen to know or find."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:82
msgid ""
"If you recognize a submission author and you&#39;re on the review "
"committee, you should not grade the submission‚Äîrecuse yourself from "
"reviewing that submission. Of course, if the process is double-blind, you"
" may not be aware that you have a conflict with it."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:83
msgid ""
"Optionally, the review team can de-anonymize after the review process to "
"ensure that the final selection is representative of the diverse grouping"
" that is desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:84
msgid "**Double Open Review**"
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:85
msgid ""
"Reviewers know who the proposal authors are and proposal authors know who"
" the reviewers are."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:86
msgid ""
"Some believe that open reviews are higher quality than anonymous "
"reviewers, as the reviewers have to stand behind their comments."
msgstr ""

#: ../DISCOVER/09_participant_selection.md:87
msgid ""
"[Sample guidelines for reviewers in double open review "
"systems](https://www.scipy2022.scipy.org/chair-reviewer-guidelines)"
